pageContext.claim: “With a pandemic, and with one of the worst things that's ever happened, we -- no -- our country has never lost 105,000 people, whether it's World Trade Center, which was 2,900, or Pearl Harbor, which was less than that. We've never lost anything close to this. But it's not only our country, is the whole world.”
pageContext.analysis: More Americans died in World War II and the Civil War than have died from covid-19.
